  "prompt": "Briefly describe the muscles of arm forearm wrist and palm?",
  "response": "The muscles of the arm, forearm, wrist, and palm work together to enable complex movements of the upper limb. Here's a brief overview:\n\n### **Arm (Brachium)**  \nThe arm contains muscles primarily responsible for elbow and shoulder movements:  \n1. **Biceps Brachii**: Flexes the elbow and supinates the forearm.  \n2. **Brachialis**: Primary flexor of the elbow.  \n3. **Triceps Brachii**: Extends the elbow.  \n4. **Coracobrachialis**: Flexes and adducts the shoulder.\n\n### **Forearm**  \nThe forearm muscles are divided into **anterior (flexor)** and **posterior (extensor)** compartments:  \n1. **Anterior Compartment**:  \n   - **Flexor Carpi Radialis/Ulnaris**: Flex and abduct/adduct the wrist.  \n   - **Palmaris Longus**: Flexes the wrist.  \n   - **Flexor Digitorum Superficialis/Profundus**: Flex the fingers.  \n   - **Pronator Teres/Quadratus**: Pronate the forearm.  \n2. **Posterior Compartment**:  \n   - **Extensor Carpi Radialis Longus/Brevis**: Extend and abduct the wrist.  \n   - **Extensor Digitorum**: Extends the fingers.  \n   - **Supinator**: Supinates the forearm.  \n   - **Brachioradialis**: Flexes the elbow (despite being in the posterior compartment).\n\n### **Wrist**  \nThe wrist is controlled by muscles originating in the forearm:  \n- Flexion: Flexor carpi radialis, flexor carpi ulnaris, palmaris longus.  \n- Extension: Extensor carpi radialis longus/brevis, extensor carpi ulnaris.  \n- Abduction/Adduction: Radial and ulnar deviation muscles.\n\n### **Palm (Hand Intrinsic Muscles)**  \nThese muscles are responsible for fine motor movements of the hand:  \n1. **Thenar Muscles**: Control thumb movements (e.g., **Opponens Pollicis**, **Abductor Pollicis Brevis**).  \n2. **Hypothenar Muscles**: Control little finger movements (e.g., **Opponens Digiti Minimi**, **Abductor Digiti Minimi**).  \n3. **Lumbricals**: Flex the metacarpophalangeal joints and extend the interphalangeal joints.  \n4. **Interossei**: Abduct and adduct the fingers (e.g., **Dorsal Interossei**, **Palmar Interossei**).  \n\nThese muscles work in tandem to provide strength, precision, and dexterity in upper limb movements.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
